festival.introText:
Turin Brakes, Don Letts, Dub Pistols Sound System, Think Floyd, Too Many T’s and 10 other excellent bands

Wick Street Festival has a very eclectic range of bands and brands to enjoy 

From indie electric folk of headliners Turin Brakes to DJ royalty Don Letts, high energy rap from Too Many T's, Dub Pistols Sound System with Barry Ashworth DJ, epic Tribute acts Think Floyd and ELO Encounter, Mudlow blues band, soaring soul singer Lady Oracle, '80's style with Miss Garbo, ceilidhs with Contraband, pop/soul from Bow, folk from Milton Hide, reggae/dub from Gumjuaka and surfer vibe from The Wave Machine...

After the live music ends at 11pm, there will be a Silent Disco

The festival site is spread across 4 roomy fields and 2 paddocks and sits beautifully under the South Downs near Lewes and Brighton.

The food and drink are almost entirely from outstanding local companies like Pished Fish, Pat's Pizzas, The 2 Fridas, Dicker Stores breakfast burritos and our very own burgers from grass fed cattle.

It's the same with the booze. We sell it very close to - and sometimes at - the same price as Pubs. Silly Moo and Ascension ciders, Beacon Down wine, Gun and Burning Sky breweries, Harley House gin and rum, Folkington's tonics, Dalston's soft drinks, Karma cola and many more.

The festival is also dog-friendly and you can even book your dog in for a gentle grooming session or just a walk.

Dates : Friday, Sep 1st and Saturday, Sep 2nd 2023 but people are welcome to camp from Thursday, August 31st under the Sussex skies but there will be no music.

faqs.question: When is Wick Street Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Wick Street Festival opens on Thursday August 31st with music on Friday 1st September and Saturday 2nd September 2023.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Does Wick Street Festival have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: Yes, Wick Street Festival has several camping options available, from standard to glamping.

faqs.question: Where is Wick Street Festival?
faqs.answer: Wick Street Festival takes place at Wick St Paddocks, Wick St, Berwick, E Sussex BN26 6TR in Polegate.

faqs.question: Does Wick Street Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Wick Street Festival. You may be asked to show photo ID.
